# NestJS Backend Standards

## Architecture

- NestJS 10, entry point `apps/api/src/main.ts`, default port 3001
- API versioning: all routes prefixed with `/v1/`
- Module structure: controllers and services under `src/modules/v1/`

## Controllers (8)

| Controller | Route Prefix | Responsibility |
|------------|-------------|----------------|
| `health` | `/v1/health` | Health check |
| `venues` | `/v1/venues` | Venue CRUD, pricing plans, seats |
| `passes` | `/v1/passes` | AccessPass purchase, transfer |
| `identity` | `/v1/identity` | Identity verification |
| `sessions` | `/v1/sessions` | Check-in / checkout |
| `user` | `/v1/user` | User balance query |
| `merchant` | `/v1/merchant` | Venue management (merchant side) |
| `compute` | `/v1/compute` | Compute nodes, job management |

## Core Services

| Service | Responsibility |
|---------|---------------|
| `StoreService` | In-memory Map data store (MVP), CRUD for all entities |
| `IdempotencyService` | Idempotency key management, prevents duplicate payments/operations |
| `LedgerService` | Ledger records, generates `ltx_`-prefixed transaction IDs |
| `FeatureFlagsService` | Feature toggles (e.g. `ENABLE_COMPUTE_MARKET`) |

## Coding Conventions

- Use `@nodestay/domain` Zod schemas for request validation
- Critical write operations (purchase, checkout) must require an `Idempotency-Key` header
- ID generation: `crypto.randomBytes(8).toString('hex')` + entity prefix
- Response messages are in **Japanese**
- Currently in-memory storage; keep Service interfaces stable for future PostgreSQL migration

## Environment Variables

- `PORT` — Server port
- `DATABASE_URL` — PostgreSQL connection string (reserved)
- `REDIS_URL` — Redis connection string (reserved)
- `JWT_SECRET` — JWT signing secret
- `ENABLE_COMPUTE_MARKET` — Compute market feature toggle
- `OPERATOR_PRIVATE_KEY` — On-chain operator private key
